Ask HN: Suggestions on storing entity-attribute-value model
text:
I'm building an attributes store for storing aggregated attribute values to be used for segmentation and targeting. I'm wondering if anyone has any suggestions for the storage of such a model.

I've been reading the following: -https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Entity%E2%80%93attribute%E2%80%93value_model - https://inviqa.com/blog/understanding-eav-data-model-and-when-use-it

but wanted to get a sense of real world usage and what storage has been used.

title: Ask HN: What would an ideal version of the internet look like?
text:
As a thought experiment what would the ideal version of the internet look like disregarding any perceived hurdles? Think of what a typical experience is today and take away all of the cruft and things that diminish the experience.

Some initial thoughts: no pay walls, no ads, no pop ups and transparent identities.

In what ways is the current path deviating or coalescing to the ideal vision?

Tell HN: I am starting Mastering Emacs book club today. You are welcome to join.
text:
Hello! I am starting a book club to study and discuss the book Mastering Emacs written by Mickey Petersen.

I did a book club like this about analytic number theory in 2021. Thanks to participants from the HN community and Libera IRC, that was completed successfully after 120 book club meetings.

This new book club is going to focus on the book Mastering Emacs. If you are interested in learning Emacs or in studying this book together with a group, you are very welcome to join!

The first meeting is today at 20:00 UTC. Schedule, meeting link, and more details are available here: https://susam.net/club/mastering-emacs/

Ask HN: Can we stop talking about Elon Musk for a while please?
text:
[0]

It is turning HN into another social media circus - sucking all energy, joy, mental bandwidth from other things here.

All I am asking for is to let it go and not pay much attention to EM related stories for some time. They are precisely to elucidate a dopamine reaction and are no longer constructive.

[0] I understand the irony about talking about not asking to talk about it. One way to go about is to not comment to this thread.
